node: second_book | Brother Faolan
  *(His eyes go wide, and the acquisitive monk's whole soul lights up at the idea of a *new* book — but a new book of an entirely new kind.)* A *second* book. *(he breathes it.)* The *Catalogue* of the *Written-After-All.* *(he's already reaching for a blank ledger, his hands shaking with a want that has, for the first time in twenty years, *hope* in it.)* *Yes* — *gods* — *yes.* *(fierce, joyous.)* Beside the *graveyard* of the *never-made*, a — a *birth-register.* And *every* *time* a *living* *maker* *crosses* *themselves* *out* of the *Unwritten* — *writes* the *thing* they *meant* to, *finally*, *late* but *done* — I *record* it *here*, in the *new* book: *"The History of the Lower City — written, at last, by the Low Lantern's keeper, forty years intended, one winter completed."* *(his voice fills.)* And the *new* book *grows*, *page* by *page*, as the *old* one *empties* — a *ledger* not of *almosts* but of *deadlines* *beaten*, of *makers* who *refused* to *become* *entries*, of *the* *world* *finally* *making* the *things* it *kept* *meaning* to. *(he meets your eyes, weeping with a joy that's been twenty years coming.)* *Candlekeep* *keeps* the *greatest* *library* in the *Realms*, Returned — and *every* *book* in it is a *thing* that *got* *made.* But *no* *one* *ever* *kept* the *record* of the *making* *itself* — the *triumph* of the *thing* *that* *almost* *wasn't* and *then* *was.* *(he grips the blank ledger.)* I'll *keep* *that* *one.* The *Catalogue* of *the* *Written-After-All.* The *only* book in *Candlekeep* whose *every* *entry* is a *small* *victory* *over* *time.* *(he beams through tears.)* *Twenty* *years* of *thin* *accessions* — and the *richest* *one* I'll *ever* *keep* is the *book* that *fills* *up* *as* *the* *saddest* *one* *empties.* *Help* me *start* it. *Entry* *one*: *Faolan's* *poems.* *Written* *after* *all.*
  enter: SET sq.unwritten_written_after_all, SET sq.faolan_writes_his_poems, SET act5.unbroken_line, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +6
  auto: close
node: heal_the_filers | Brother Faolan
  *(He goes quiet, and his hand drifts to his own page, and the truth of it lands on him with the weight of twenty years.)* Heal the *cataloguers.* *(quietly.)* The *people* *first.* *(he looks around the library — the silent scholars, the bent readers, the filers of others' words.)* You've — *(his voice catches)* — you've *named* the *disease* of this *whole* *place.* *(he meets your eyes.)* *Every* *one* of *us* — the *First* *Readers*, the *Acquisitions* *monks*, the *cataloguers* *bent* over *other* *people's* *words* — *every* *one* of *us* *was*, *once*, a *person* with *something* to *say.* And we *took* *vows*, or *got* *busy*, or *got* *scared*, and we *shelved* *ourselves* — became *people* who *file* what *others* *made* *because* it's *safer* than *risking* *making* *something* and *finding* it *isn't* *good* *enough.* *(his voice fills.)* The *Catalogue* of the *Unwritten* isn't *just* *half* *full* of the *Faithless.* It's *half* *full* of *us* — the *living*, the *shelved*, the *scholars* who *chose* the *locked* *case* over the *blank* *page.* *(fierce now.)* So *don't* just *work* the *book.* *Heal* the *makers* who *became* *filers.* *Find* every *monk* and *reader* who *quit* *creating* to *catalogue* — and *hand* *each* of them *their* *own* *page*, the way you *handed* *me* *mine.* *(he grips the Catalogue.)* Let the *Catalogue* of the *Unwritten* go *through* *Candlekeep* like a *gentle* *plague* of its *own* — *un-shelving* the *people*, *one* *abandoned* *youth* at a *time*, *reminding* *every* *scholar* who *forgot* that they were *once* a *maker* that they're *not* *dead* *yet*, *just* *late.* *(he meets your eyes, and there is a whole library's worth of liberation in it.)* The *saddest* *library* in the *world*, you'll *find*, is *not* the *Sealed* *Stacks.* It's the *one* *each* of *these* *scholars* *keeps* *locked* *inside* their *own* *quit* *youth.* *Help* me *open* *those.* *Heal* the *filers.* *Give* *Candlekeep* *back* its *makers.* *That's* the *deepest* *un-writing* of *all.*
  enter: SET sq.unwritten_heal_the_filers, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.ilfaeril +6
  auto: close
node: deflect | Brother Faolan
  *(He waves a hand, the old acquisitive fever flickering up to cover the wound, and clutches the Catalogue to his chest.)* No, no — it's a *book*, a *rare* one, my *career*, my *accession* — I'll *file* it, *catalogue* it *properly*, *secure* it in the *Stacks* where it *belongs* — *(but his eyes keep dropping to his own page, and his voice falters.)* That's — that's all it *is.* A *book* to be *shelved.* *Twenty* years I *wanted* it and now I *have* it and I'll *do* with it what *Acquisitions* *does* with *everything*: *lock* it *safe.* *(he won't meet your eyes.)* Don't — don't make it *more* than that. A *book* of *never-written* *things*, *locked* *away*, *unread* — that's — that's *fitting*, isn't it. That's *where* it *belongs.* With *all* the *other* *things* I *shelved* and *never* *opened* *again.* *(and he turns away, the Catalogue of the Unwritten pressed to his chest, the monk who filed his own youth twenty years ago reaching, by reflex, for the lock instead of the pen — but he does not walk away, and his thumb rests, trembling, on the page that is his.)*
  auto: close
node: close | Brother Faolan
  *(Brother Faolan holds the Catalogue of the Unwritten — the index of everything the world meant to make and didn't, half of it the unmade works of the Faithless the Wall took mid-creation, one page of it his own shelved youth — and whether you turned it into a funeral for the dead makers, a goad to the living ones, an indictment of the Wall's deepest and least-counted theft, a birth-register of deadlines beaten, a gentle plague that un-shelved the cataloguers themselves, or watched him reach for the lock by reflex, you carry away the strangest grief the long road names: that the Wall's cruelty was never only the souls it took, but everything those souls were still going to make — and that the saddest library in the Realms is the one each of us keeps locked inside our own abandoned youth, where the books we meant to write wait, unwritten but not yet impossible, for the day we remember we are only late.)*
